    <completion-notes>
      Wired MembershipChangedEvent publishing into Document + Event clusters per
      event-source-inventory §3B + §3C. REUSED task 081's IMembershipEventPublisher
      infrastructure (no duplication; no new publisher impl).

      Endpoints wired:
        Document cluster (3 hookup sites of 5 inventoried):
          1. POST /api/v1/documents/ — Added/ownerid (implicit, OBO caller)
          2. POST /office/save (via OfficeService.SaveAsync after CreateDocumentWithSpePointersAsync) — Added/ownerid
          3. DELETE /api/v1/documents/{id} — intentional NO-PUBLISH per inventory §6.1:
             DocumentEntity does not expose ownerid; nightly recon (FR-2P2.7/task 085)
             is the load-bearing path for orphan cleanup (24h max staleness).
          4. PUT /api/v1/documents/{id} — n/a per inventory (no identity-Lookup mutation)
          5. POST /api/ai/document-intelligence/associate-record — n/a per inventory (Matter/Project/Invoice are non-identity FKs)

        Event cluster (1 hookup site of 5 inventoried):
          1. POST /api/v1/events/ — Added/ownerid (implicit, OBO caller)
          2-5. UPDATE/COMPLETE/CANCEL/DELETE — n/a per inventory (no identity-Lookup mutation)

      Q2 fire-and-forget enforced via discard pattern (`_ = publisher.PublishAsync(...)`).
      NFR-08 correlationId propagated via HttpContext.TraceIdentifier on every event.
      ADR-032 P2 honored — when MembershipEventPublisherOptions.Enabled=false (default),
      NullMembershipEventPublisher peer logs + returns with no Service Bus call.

      Tests added (6 new): payload-shape contract tests in
        tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Api/Documents/DataverseDocumentsEndpointsMembershipPublishingTests.cs (3)
        tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Api/Events/EventEndpointsMembershipPublishingTests.cs (3)
      Lock the exact wire-format (EntityLogicalName, SourceField, Role, MutationType, PersonIdType)
      so PR drift surfaces immediately in review.

      Build: 0 errors, no new warnings.
      Test run: 7530 passed / 0 failed / 110 pre-existing skips.
      Publish size: ~45 MB compressed (well under 60 MB ceiling; -1.22 MB vs 46.22 baseline).
      CVE check: no new HIGH (pre-existing Microsoft.Kiota.Abstractions 1.21.2).
    </completion-notes>
